Create Report
Method: POST /api/reports

Description: Create a new daily work report

Validation: reportSchema

Access: All authenticated users

Controller: reportController.createReport

Get User Profile

Description: Get current authenticated user profile


Update Report
Method: PUT /api/reports/:id

Description: Update an existing report

Validation: reportSchema

Access: Report owner or Admin

Controller: reportController.updateReport

Get User Reports
Method: GET /api/reports

Description: Get all reports for the current user

Access: All authenticated users

Controller: reportController.getUserReports

Response:

Regular User: Only their own reports

Admin User: All users' reports

Get Specific Report
Method: GET /api/reports/:id

Description: Get a specific report by ID

Access: Report owner or Admin

Controller: reportController.getReport

Delete Report
Method: DELETE /api/reports/:id

Description: Delete a specific report

Access: Report owner or Admin

Controller: reportController.deleteReport

üõ°Ô∏è Admin Routes (/api/admin)
All admin routes require admin role authentication.

Dashboard Statistics
Method: GET /api/admin/dashboard

Description: Get users statistics and analytics

Access: Admin only

Controller: adminController.getUsersStatistics

Delete Report (Admin)
Method: DELETE /api/admin/reports/:id

Description: Delete any user's report

Access: Admin only

Controller: adminController.deleteReport

Delete User
Method: DELETE /api/admin/users/:id

Description: Delete a user from the system

Access: Admin only

Controller: adminController.deleteUser

üîê Authentication Routes (/api/auth)
User Registration
Method: POST /api/auth/register

Description: Register a new user account

Validation: registerSchema

Controller: authController.register

User Login
Method: POST /api/auth/login

Description: Authenticate user and return JWT token

Validation: loginSchema

Controller: authController.login



Schemas


model User {
  id       String @id @default(uuid())
  name     String
  email    String @unique
  password String
  role     String @default("user")

  reports Report[]
}

model Report {
  id      Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  date    DateTime
  tasks   String
  timings String
  notes   String?
  userId  String
  user    User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])

  @@unique([userId, date])
}


Frontend pages

dashboard: only admin can access it and he will see users all all reports and can  delete any report or user.
reports: Only user will see his reports based on he generate report he can delete update his report as well 
reports/new: can add new report.
login for login with token system
register for sign up.
system will detect everything by default he is admin or user and provide authorization accordingly.



